# Swift & iOS Rules
- Always use Swift 6 / Swift 2026 idioms.
- Prefer `@Observable` over `ObservableObject`.
- Use `Group` or `Section` in SwiftUI to avoid deeply nested view hierarchies.
- When creating new Views, include:
    ```swift
    #if DEBUG
    @ObserveInjection var inject
    #endif
    // ... at end of body:
    .enableInjection()
    ```

# Modularization Rules
- Business logic belongs in `Domain`.
- API and Persistence belong in `Data`.
- Views belong in `Feature[Name]` modules.
- Never import a Feature module into another Feature module (use the Coordinator).

# AI Rules
- Use `gemini-2.0-flash` for all AIService calls.
- Ensure API keys are never hardcoded; suggest `Secrets.plist` or Environment Variables.